---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout title="About AIForEdu" description="Why AIForEdu exists, how it is published, and how its review process is intended to support school leadership decisions.">
  <section class="page-hero section-shell-tight">
    <div class="container-full">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1 class="mt-6 page-title">Built to help school leaders make better AI decisions.</h1>
        <p class="page-lede">AIForEdu exists to turn a noisy category into something more legible for district and school leadership.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell-tight">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-shell">
        <p>AIForEdu.ai is the independent AI-in-education library built for K-12 school leaders who want to adopt AI responsibly — without the vendor hype.</p>
        <p>We publish tool reviews, policy resources, and implementation guidance intended to help superintendents, principals, district leads, and school teams make more defensible AI decisions.</p>
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>Every school leader in America should have access to trustworthy, practical guidance for bringing AI into their schools. Cost should never be a barrier to responsible AI adoption.</p>
        <p>That's why our core library — tool reviews, policy templates, and guides — is 100% free. Our premium products exist for leaders who want done-for-you toolkits that save weeks of work.</p>
        <h2>How We Review Tools</h2>
        <p>Every tool on AIForEdu.ai is reviewed against the same broad framework: privacy posture, instructional value, implementation readiness, and transparency. The methodology page explains how we distinguish vendor claims, reviewed documentation, and operational observations.</p>
        <p>We accept affiliate relationships with some tools we review, but editorial independence remains the rule. Affiliate links, if present, should never be the only reason a product appears on the site.</p>
        <h2>Who We Are</h2>
        <p>AIForEdu.ai is a product of <a href="https://imglocal.com">Impact Glocal Inc.</a>. At the moment, the site is published by the Impact Glocal editorial and research team rather than by a fully bylined contributor roster. Public contributor and advisor profiles should be added as the library expands.</p>
        <h2>What We Will Not Claim</h2>
        <p>AIForEdu should not imply district approval, legal validation, field testing, or market leadership unless those statements can be supported. Where a detail comes from vendor materials and has not been independently corroborated, the site should say so.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10">
        <div class="cta-panel">
          <p class="section-label">Read the method</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-display-xs text-ink-950">Want the review standards in full?</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-7 text-ink-500">See the public methodology for scoring pillars, evidence levels, affiliate policy, and update standards.</p>
          <div class="mt-5">
            <a href="/methodology/" class="btn-primary">Review methodology</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6">
          <NewsletterSignup variant="banner" heading="Get the weekly briefing" subheading="A concise research note for school leadership teams tracking AI." />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
